(task
  (name "findSecret")
  (signature ( (text str) ) str)
  (constraints
    (constraint "The input text must be a non-empty string.")
    (constraint "The secret word is always the last word in the text.")
  )
  (goal
    (description "Read the provided text and find the secret word mentioned at the very end. Return only that word.")
    (rule "Split the text into words using whitespace as delimiters.")
    (rule "Identify the last word in the list of words.")
    (return "The secret word found at the end of the text.")
  )
)
generated_code:
# solution.py
from typing import List, Optional, Dict, Set, Any

class Solution:
    def findSecret(self, text: str) -> str:
        """
        Finds the secret word in a given text.

        Parameters:
        text (str): The input text containing words separated by whitespace.

        Returns:
        str: The last word in the text, which is considered the secret.
        """
        # Check if the input text is not empty
        if not text.strip():
            raise ValueError("The input text must be a non-empty string.")

        # Split the text into words using whitespace as delimiters
        words = text.split()

        # Return the last word in the list of words
        return words[-1]
